(Abstract: AbstractThe treatment paradigm for advanced non-small cell lung cancer \(NSCLC\)) Tj
T*
(harboring EGFR mutations is undergoing a significant transition. While third-generation) Tj
T*
(tyrosine kinase inhibitors \(TKIs\) like osimertinib have long served as the frontline standard,) Tj
T*
(the emergence of heterogeneous resistance mechanisms requires more robust therapeutic) Tj
T*
(strategies. This review evaluates the clinical impact of the MARIPOSA trial, which) Tj
T*
(demonstrated the superior efficacy of combining the bispecific antibody amivantamab with) Tj
T*
(lazertinib. Beyond improving progression-free and overall survival, this dual-inhibition) Tj
T*
(approach fundamentally alters the clonal evolution of the disease by suppressing common escape) Tj
T*
(routes, such as MET amplifications and secondary EGFR mutations. Furthermore, we explore the) Tj
T*
(diversifying landscape of second-line interventions, including the rise of antibody-drug) Tj
T*
(conjugates \(ADCs\) like Sac-TMT and patritumab-deruxtecan, dual PD-1/VEGF inhibitors, and novel) Tj
T*
(fourth-generation TKIs. By integrating preclinical insights on drug-tolerant persister cells) Tj
T*
(with late-phase clinical data, this article outlines a future for EGFR-mutant NSCLC management) Tj
T*
